iewpoint route.","tip":"Wind matters here. Even on clear days, the coast can feel stronger and cooler than inland stops."}},{"number":3,"time":"12:15","duration":"60 min","name":"Lunch","category":"Midday Reset","description":"Lunch is not filler on this route. It is the reset point that keeps the second half strong, especially before Jeongbang and the final Seongsan push.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1414235077428-338989a2e8c0?w=800&q=80","highlights":["A true recovery point in a fast-paced route","Better energy balance before the eastern transfer","Useful for mixed-age active groups","Prevents the day from feeling over-compressed"],"timeUsed":["Arrival and seating","Meal and short rest","Departure prep for the late-day route"],"whyOnRoute":"Placed here, lunch protects the quality of the afternoon instead of turning the route into pure transit.","visitBasics":{"hours":"Restaurant hours","closed":"Varies","admission":"Pay directly unless otherwise stated","walking":"Minimal"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Restaurant facilities","parking":"Available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"Food shots work well here if you want a break from landscape-heavy photos.","facilities":"Full restaurant amenities.","tip":"This stop matters because the route is stronger when the group resets well rather than rushes through lunch."}},{"number":4,"time":"13:35","duration":"50 min","name":"Jeongbang Waterfall","category":"Waterfall to Sea","description":"Jeongbang changes the mood again. After lunch, the route becomes more textured and coastal, with stone steps, sea spray, and a stop that feels distinctly south Jeju rather than generic waterfall sightseeing.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1441974231531-c6227db76b6e?w=800&q=80","highlights":["Waterfall and rocky coast in one compact stop","A stronger textural contrast after lunch","Late-day scenic momentum before the eastern transfer","Good visual variety within a high-density route"],"timeUsed":["Arrival and entrance setup","Main waterfall viewing segment","Photos, short pause, and return"],"whyOnRoute":"It keeps the south-coast section memorable before the longer move east toward Seongsan.","visitBasics":{"hours":"09:00-17:20","closed":"Open year-round","admission":"Adults 2,000 / Children 1,000 KRW","walking":"Moderate with steps"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Entrance area","parking":"Available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"The lower rocky area gives the best mood shots, but footing and spray can affect comfort.","facilities":"Basic facilities near the entrance.","tip":"The stairs and rock approach make this feel more active than it first looks on the map."}},{"number":5,"time":"15:25","duration":"70 min","name":"Seongsan Ilchulbong","category":"Crater Finale","description":"Seongsan closes the day with the island''s most iconic landmark. After Hallasan, the south coast, and Jeongbang, this final stop gives the route a real sense of completion rather than a soft finish.","image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1596402184320-417e7178b2cd?w=800&q=80","highlights":["A signature Jeju landmark to close the route","Strong visual reward at the end of a dense day","Summit or base-area experience depending on group pace","A clear finale for first-time visitors with limited time"],"timeUsed":["Arrival, orientation, and pace check","Main walking segment or base-area viewing","Photos and regroup before Jeju City return"],"whyOnRoute":"Placed last, Seongsan works as the strongest final landmark and gives the route a true grand-finale effect.","visitBasics":{"hours":"Seasonal hours; ticketed entry varies by season","closed":"First Monday of each month (or following day if Monday is a public holiday)","admission":"Adults 5,000 / Children 2,500 KRW","walking":"Moderate to challenging if summit"},"convenience":{"restroom":"Base area and nearby facilities","parking":"Large parking area available"},"smartNotes":{"photo":"Wider crater and coastline views usually land better than tight summit-only shots.