egional tour."}]},{"title":"Why the day feels strong","icon":"mountain","iconBg":"bg-sky-50/80","iconColor":"text-sky-600","items":[{"label":"Two More Active Sections","detail":"Eoseungsaengak and Seongsan make this more active than our regular small-group routes."},{"label":"Scenic Density Over Slow Pacing","detail":"This route is designed for travelers who want more of Jeju in one day, not for guests looking for a slow sightseeing rhythm."},{"label":"Worth It If Time Is Short","detail":"For travelers with only one day, the route trades a gentler pace for stronger iconic coverage."}]},{"title":"When conditions shift","icon":"wind","iconBg":"bg-slate-50/80","iconColor":"text-slate-600","items":[{"label":"Hallasan Controls","detail":"Trail access at Eoseungsaengak can be affected by seasonal rules and weather controls."},{"label":"Wind at Coastal Stops","detail":"Jusangjeolli and Seongsan are the two most weather-sensitive scenic segments of the day."},{"label":"Return Time Can Shift","detail":"Traffic, walking pace, and on-site crowd conditions can shift the final return time slightly."}]}]},"practicalAccordionItems":[{"id":"pickup","title":"Pickup & return timing","preview":"Early start, late return to Jeju City","content":["Pickup from Jeju City area between 08:30-09:00","Return to Jeju City approximately 17:40-18:00","Airport pickup or drop-off may be available on request","Exact meeting time is confirmed the evening before"]},{"id":"walking","title":"Walking & terrain","preview":"More active than our standard routes","content":["This route includes two more active walking sections","Eoseungsaengak involves uphill walking and stairs","Jeongbang includes steps and a rock-side approach","Seongsan can feel demanding if the summit route is taken","Comfortable walking shoes are strongly recommended"]},{"id":"weather","title":"Weather & closure handling","preview":"Runs in most conditions with adjustments","content":["Light rain: tour usually proceeds with normal adjustments","Strong wind: coastal exposure at Jusangjeolli or Seongsan may be shortened","Hallasan trail controls: Eoseungsaengak may be replaced or adjusted if access is restricted","Site closures: alternative pacing or replacement stops may be used when needed"]},{"id":"flight","title":"For same-day arrival or departure","preview":"Strong for one-day visitors, with time buffer","content":["This route is designed for travelers who want Jeju''s biggest highlights in one day","It can work well for same-day arrival or departure guests","Evening departures are recommended","Please allow generous buffer time for traffic and walking conditions"]},{"id":"wear","title":"What to wear & bring","preview":"Walking shoes, layers, light wind protection","content":["Walking shoes with good grip","Layers for mountain and coastal temperature changes","Light wind-resistant jacket","Hat and sunscreen","Water bottle"]},{"id":"included","title":"Included / not included","preview":"Guide, vehicle, pickup, admission fees","variant":"included","content":["Professional English-speaking guide","Small-group vehicle","Hotel pickup/drop-off (Jeju City)","All admission fees","Bottled water","Lunch (pay directly at restaurant)","Personal shopping","Gratuities"]}],"practicalWeatherStatic":{"today":{"temp":"—","label":"Live weather shown at runtime"},"tomorrow":{"temp":"—","label":"Updated daily"}},"seasonalVariations":[{"name":"Spring","icon":"flower","description":"Fresh mountain air and cleaner visibility across the island loop","tag":"Balanced season","bgClass":"bg-spring","iconColor":"text-pink-500"},{"name":"Summer","icon":"sun","description":"Longer daylight and stronger coastal color","tag":"Longest days","bgClass":"bg-summer","iconColor":"text-sky-500"},{"name":"Autumn","icon":"leaf","description":"Crisp visibility makes the route feel especially rewarding","tag":"Best clarity","bgClass":"bg-autumn","iconColor":"text-amber-600"},{"name":"Winter","icon":"snow","description":"Sharper air, more 